---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is custom software development?",
    answer: "Custom software development is the process of designing, building, and maintaining applications tailored to a specific business's workflows and goals, rather than buying off-the-shelf tools that force you to adapt to them.",
  },
  {
    question: "How long does it take to build a custom software product?",
    answer: "Most projects ship a working version in 6–12 weeks. Internal tools and dashboards can be ready in 4–6 weeks; full platforms and SaaS products take 3–6 months depending on scope and integrations.",
  },
  {
    question: "Do you build for web, mobile, or both?",
    answer: "Both. We design responsive web applications, native iOS/Android apps, and cross-platform builds (React Native) that share a single codebase across devices.",
  },
  {
    question: "Will the software scale as our business grows?",
    answer: "Yes. We use scalable architecture patterns, managed cloud infrastructure (AWS, Vercel, Firebase), and modular code so the system can support 10× the load without a rewrite.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Custom Software Development Company"
  description="Custom software development company building scalable web apps, mobile apps, internal tools, and business automation platforms for businesses worldwide. Based in Kannur, Kerala."
  keywords="custom software development, custom software development company, web application development, mobile app development, business automation, scalable software, enterprise software development, custom software India, software development Kerala"
  service={{
    name: "Custom Software Development",
    description: "End-to-end custom software development services covering web applications, mobile apps, internal tools, and business automation systems built for scale and performance.",
    serviceType: "Custom Software Development",
  }}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <Navbar />

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero__glow"></div>
    <div class="page-hero__bg-dots"></div>
    <div class="container page-hero__inner">
      <div class="badge badge-sky">Custom Software</div>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">
        Custom Software <span class="text-gradient">Development Company</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="page-hero__desc">
        We design and build tailored web applications, mobile apps, and business automation platforms for companies that need software that fits how they actually work, not the other way around.
      </p>
      <div class="page-hero__cta">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Start Your Project</a>
        <a href="/work/" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">See Our Work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-section">
    <div class="container content-narrow">

      <h2>Why choose custom over off-the-shelf software?</h2>
      <p>
        Off-the-shelf tools are quick to start with, but they force you to bend your processes around someone else's assumptions. Custom software flips that around. It is built to match the exact workflow, integrations, and reporting needs of your business, which means less manual work, fewer workarounds, and a system that grows with you instead of holding you back.
      </p>
      <p>
        For most growing businesses, the moment to invest in custom software arrives when three things happen at once: spreadsheets break under volume, your team loses hours to repetitive tasks, and the tool you bought stops fitting how you actually work. A well-built custom platform pays for itself within months by reclaiming that time.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're a <a href="/software-development-company-kannur/">Kannur, Kerala-based team</a> that has built custom platforms for auto service workshops, fitness studios, wooden-flooring brands, aviation operators, and SMBs across India and the Gulf. Local engagement when you want it, video calls and Slack when you don't.
      </p>

      <h2>What we build</h2>

      <h3>Web applications</h3>
      <p>
        Customer portals, internal dashboards, marketplaces, booking systems, and data-heavy admin panels. We build with React, Next.js, Astro, and Node.js: frameworks that load fast, scale predictably, and are easy for any developer to maintain later.
      </p>

      <h3>Mobile apps (iOS &amp; Android)</h3>
      <p>
        Native and cross-platform mobile applications using React Native and Flutter. From customer-facing apps with real-time features to internal field-staff tools that work offline, we ship apps that feel native on every device.
      </p>

      <h3>Internal tools and dashboards</h3>
      <p>
        Replace fragile spreadsheets and manual processes with internal tools your operations, sales, and finance teams actually want to use. Real-time data, role-based access, and automation rules built in.
      </p>

      <h3>Business automation and integrations</h3>
      <p>
        Connect the systems your business already runs on (CRM, ERP, payment gateways, email tools, third-party APIs) and automate the repetitive workflows in between. Less copy-paste, faster decisions, fewer human errors.
      </p>

      <h2>Our development process</h2>
      <p>
        We work in short, transparent cycles so you see progress every week, not every quarter.
      </p>
      <ol class="content-list">
        <li><strong>Discovery.</strong> We map your workflows, talk to the people who will use the software, and define the smallest version that delivers value.</li>
        <li><strong>Design.</strong> Wireframes, prototypes, and a clickable design system so you can validate the experience before a single line of production code is written.</li>
        <li><strong>Build.</strong> Weekly demos, version control, automated testing, and continuous deployment to a staging environment you can use anytime.</li>
        <li><strong>Launch and support.</strong> We handle the production launch and stay on as a long-term technology partner for updates, monitoring, and new features.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Technologies we use</h2>
      <p>
        Our stack changes with the project, but most of our work runs on <strong>React, Next.js, Astro, Node.js, React Native, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Firebase,</strong> and <strong>AWS</strong>. We choose tools based on the problem, not on what's trendy, and we document everything so handoff is clean if you ever change partners.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      {faqs.map(f => (
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>{f.question}</h3>
          <p>{f.answer}</p>
        </div>
      ))}

      <div class="page-cta">
        <h2>Ready to build something tailored to your business?</h2>
        <p>Tell us about your idea or workflow problem. We'll respond within 24 hours with a tailored proposal covering scope, timeline, and price.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary btn-xl">Start a Project</a>
        <p class="page-cta__note">
          Curious about our SaaS work too? See our <a href="/saas-development-company/">SaaS development services</a> or browse <a href="/work/">recent client projects</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: calc(80px + 4rem) 0 4rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fafc 0%, #ffffff 100%);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero__glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 800px; height: 400px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(14,165,233,0.18) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .page-hero__inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .page-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .page-hero__desc {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--gray-600);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .page-hero__cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn-lg { padding: 0.85rem 2rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .btn-xl { padding: 1rem 2.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }

  .content-section { padding: 4rem 0 6rem; }
  .content-narrow { max-width: 800px; }
  .content-narrow h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .content-narrow h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .content-narrow h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--gray-900);
  }
  .content-narrow p {
    color: var(--gray-700);
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }
  .content-list {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    color: var(--gray-700);
    line-height: 1.85;
  }
  .content-list li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--gray-600);
  }

  .page-cta {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding: 3rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--gray-900), var(--sky-900));
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .page-cta h2 {
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  }
  .page-cta p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .page-cta__note {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  }
  .page-cta__note a {
    color: var(--sky-300);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
